GIF Viewer deferred startup command-line load
============================================

Purpose
-------

When a large GIF was opened directly from Explorer/file association, the form
constructor processed the command-line file immediately. That caused helper
predecode to finish before the main window appeared.

This change stores the initial command-line arguments and processes them from
the first Shown event using BeginInvoke, allowing the window to paint before
the expensive GIF load starts. In-app file opens and subsequent single-instance
command-line opens continue to use the existing immediate ProcessCommandLine
path.

Files changed
-------------

- source/FormMain.cs

Patch
-----

```diff
diff --git a/source/FormMain.cs b/source/FormMain.cs
--- a/source/FormMain.cs
+++ b/source/FormMain.cs
@@
         /// <summary>
         /// Windows' Open File Dialog:
         /// </summary>
         private readonly OpenFileDialog _op = new OpenFileDialog();
+
+        /// <summary>
+        /// Command-line arguments to process after the form is first shown.
+        /// </summary>
+        private string[] _initialCommandLineArgs;
@@
-            ProcessCommandLine(args);
+            if (args != null && args.Length > 0 && File.Exists(args[0]))
+                _initialCommandLineArgs = args;
+            else
+                ProcessCommandLine(args);
@@
         private void Form1_Shown(object sender, EventArgs e)
         {
             AllowDrop = true;
 
+            if (_initialCommandLineArgs != null)
+            {
+                string[] args = _initialCommandLineArgs;
+                _initialCommandLineArgs = null;
+                BeginInvoke(new Action(() => ProcessCommandLine(args)));
+                return;
+            }
+
             if (!_openFile)
                 return;
```

